{{infobox country at games | NPC = EGY | NPCname = Egyptian Paralympic Committee | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1996 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] | competitors = 31 (26 men and 5 women) | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 21 | gold = 8 | silver = 11 | bronze = 11 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 1972 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Egypt]]''' competed at the '''[[1996 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Atlanta]], [[United States]]. They sent 31 athletes (26 males and 5 females), who won 30 total medals, 8 gold, 11 silver and 11 bronze. They participated in several sports including powerlifting.<ref name="paralympic.org">{{Cite web|url=http://www.paralympic.org/Athletes/Results|title=Atlanta 1996 Paralympic Games: Egypt|accessdate=2012-08-27|work=paralympic.org}}</ref> The team included powerlifters [[Ahmed Gomaa Mohamed Ahmed]] and [[Metwalli Mathana]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/News/17317/26/On-to-the-Paralympics.aspx|title=On to the Paralympics|last=|first=|date=September 8, 2016|work=Al-Ahram Weekly|issue=1311|access-date=October 25, 2016|via=}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://bmsi.ru/doc/4b08ed1c-91be-4945-873d-89b8abdf840a|title=Meet Ahmed, Multi Gold Medal Winner and Paralympic Record Holder - Популярные статьи - Библиотека международной спортивной информации|website=bmsi.ru|access-date=2016-10-26}}</ref>
