{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''Hand guards''' are devices worn by athletes in [[artistic gymnastics]]. Various types of hand guards are used by gymnasts:

* '''[[Grip (gymnastics)|Grip]]s''' are used on the [[uneven bars]], [[high bar]], [[still rings]] and [[parallel bars]] to enhance the gymnast's grip and, in the case of bar exercises, to reduce friction between the gymnast's hands and the bar.
* '''Braces''' do not offer the gymnast any performance advantage, but help to prevent injury by providing support and lessening impact on the wrists and hands. {{Clarify|date=February 2009}}
* '''Wrist guards''' are usually worn by male gymnasts performing on the [[pommel horse]], and sometimes by female gymnasts on the [[floor exercise]] or [[vault (gymnastics)|vault]]. {{Clarify|date=February 2009}}

