[[File:Randy carrasco qs wax comb.jpg|thumb|right|250px]]
A '''wax comb''' is a tool used in the maintenance and removal of [[surfboard wax]] on a [[surfboard]]. Wax combs typically have features such a jagged or toothed edge and a straight, relatively sharp edge. The jagged edge is used to create textured grooves for improving the traction of the wax and the straight edge is used for scraping off unwanted wax.<ref>{{cite web|last=Curtin|first=Ryan|title=How To Use A Surfboard Wax Comb|url=http://www.mademan.com/mm/how-use-surfboard-wax-comb.html}}</ref>  In addition to the straight edge for wax removal, some wax combs even have an inwardly curved edge for the rails (such as [[Mr. Zog's Sex Wax]] “Sex Comb”).<ref>{{cite web|title=Surf Wax 101|url=http://www.surfinghandbook.com/knowledge/beginners-surfing-tips/surf-wax/}}</ref> Additionally, wax combs can have features such as [[FCS (fins)|fin]] key, [[bottle opener]] or a snap for portability (attachment to interior pocket loop, lanyard or leash attachment lanyard).<ref>{{cite web|title=Surfing Wales: Wax|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/wales/surfing/sites/learn/pages/wax.shtml}}</ref>

